[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":580},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fjsweirdworld\u002F2019\u002F05\u002F16\u002Fjs-weird-world-09-variable-environments\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fjsweirdworld\u002F2019\u002F05\u002F16\u002Fjs-weird-world-09-variable-environments\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fjsweirdworld\u002F2019\u002F05\u002F16\u002Fjs-weird-world-09-variable-environments\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fjsweirdworld\u002F2019\u002F05\u002F16\u002Fjs-weird-world-09-variable-environments\u002F":557,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fjsweirdworld\u002F2019\u002F05\u002F16\u002Fjs-weird-world-09-variable-environments\u002F":566},"\u002Fjsweirdworld\u002F20190516\u002F2342284884\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":541,"date":542,"description":543,"extension":544,"lang":545,"meta":546,"navigation":44,"path":547,"readingMinutes":548,"seo":549,"standalone":550,"stem":551,"tags":552,"tldr":554,"updated":542,"url":555,"__hash__":556},"content\u002Fen\u002FJsWeirdWorld\u002Fjs-weird-world-09-variable-environments.md","[JS Weird World] No.9 Functions, Execution Context, and the Variable Environment","1000530576",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":537},"minimark",[11,16,24,27,150,168,196,199,204,216,345,348,354,368,375,507,512,521,525,533],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"the-variable-environment","The Variable Environment",[17,18,19],"p",{},[20,21],"img",{"alt":22,"src":23},"The variable environment","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002F8bmAajf.png",[17,25,26],{},"The variable environment is really just about where you create your variables. Basically, all you need to care about is \"where\" a variable was created. The course also gives us a little snippet to play with:",[28,29,34],"pre",{"className":30,"code":31,"language":32,"meta":33,"style":33},"language-js shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","\nfunction b() {\n var myVar;\n}\n\nfunction a() {\n var myVar = 2;\n b();\n}\n\nvar myVar = 1;\na();\n","js","",[35,36,37,46,61,70,76,81,91,109,117,122,127,142],"code",{"__ignoreMap":33},[38,39,42],"span",{"class":40,"line":41},"line",1,[38,43,45],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":44},true,"\n",[38,47,49,53,57],{"class":40,"line":48},2,[38,50,52],{"class":51},"sWyjQ","function",[38,54,56],{"class":55},"sj_SG"," b",[38,58,60],{"class":59},"sMAXC","() {\n",[38,62,64,67],{"class":40,"line":63},3,[38,65,66],{"class":51}," var",[38,68,69],{"class":59}," myVar;\n",[38,71,73],{"class":40,"line":72},4,[38,74,75],{"class":59},"}\n",[38,77,79],{"class":40,"line":78},5,[38,80,45],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":44},[38,82,84,86,89],{"class":40,"line":83},6,[38,85,52],{"class":51},[38,87,88],{"class":55}," a",[38,90,60],{"class":59},[38,92,94,96,99,102,106],{"class":40,"line":93},7,[38,95,66],{"class":51},[38,97,98],{"class":59}," myVar ",[38,100,101],{"class":51},"=",[38,103,105],{"class":104},"sCcAr"," 2",[38,107,108],{"class":59},";\n",[38,110,112,114],{"class":40,"line":111},8,[38,113,56],{"class":55},[38,115,116],{"class":59},"();\n",[38,118,120],{"class":40,"line":119},9,[38,121,75],{"class":59},[38,123,125],{"class":40,"line":124},10,[38,126,45],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":44},[38,128,130,133,135,137,140],{"class":40,"line":129},11,[38,131,132],{"class":51},"var",[38,134,98],{"class":59},[38,136,101],{"class":51},[38,138,139],{"class":104}," 1",[38,141,108],{"class":59},[38,143,145,148],{"class":40,"line":144},12,[38,146,147],{"class":55},"a",[38,149,116],{"class":59},[17,151,152,153,156,157,160,161,164,165,167],{},"Notice that ",[35,154,155],{},"var myVar"," shows up in three places: inside ",[35,158,159],{},"a()",", inside ",[35,162,163],{},"b()",", and in the global environment. So what actually happens when ",[35,166,159],{}," runs? Let's go back to the idea from the \"execution context\" chapter.",[169,170,171,179,187],"ol",{},[172,173,174,175,178],"li",{},"The global environment creates a ",[35,176,177],{},"myVar",".",[172,180,181,182,184,185,178],{},"The execution context for ",[35,183,159],{}," creates its own ",[35,186,177],{},[172,188,189,190,192,193,178],{},"The execution context for the last function creates ",[35,191,177],{}," too, but this one is ",[35,194,195],{},"undefined",[17,197,198],{},"Just like this diagram from the course:",[17,200,201],{},[20,202],{"alt":22,"src":203},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FGbPXppx.png",[17,205,206,207,209,210,212,213,215],{},"Each variable has its own slot of memory, and they don't interfere with the global one or with ",[35,208,159],{}," or ",[35,211,163],{},". All of this ties back to something called \"scope\" — basically where we're allowed to see a given variable. Every variable only shows up inside the execution context where we defined it. So even though ",[35,214,177],{}," got created three times, the three never affect each other. Let's prove it:",[28,217,219],{"className":30,"code":218,"language":32,"meta":33,"style":33},"function b() {\n var myVar;\n console.log(myVar);\n}\n\nfunction a() {\n var myVar = 2;\n console.log(myVar);\n b();\n}\n\nvar myVar = 1;\nconsole.log(myVar);\na();\nconsole.log('what is a now?:'+ myVar);\n",[35,220,221,229,235,246,250,254,262,274,282,288,292,296,308,318,325],{"__ignoreMap":33},[38,222,223,225,227],{"class":40,"line":41},[38,224,52],{"class":51},[38,226,56],{"class":55},[38,228,60],{"class":59},[38,230,231,233],{"class":40,"line":48},[38,232,66],{"class":51},[38,234,69],{"class":59},[38,236,237,240,243],{"class":40,"line":63},[38,238,239],{"class":59}," console.",[38,241,242],{"class":55},"log",[38,244,245],{"class":59},"(myVar);\n",[38,247,248],{"class":40,"line":72},[38,249,75],{"class":59},[38,251,252],{"class":40,"line":78},[38,253,45],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":44},[38,255,256,258,260],{"class":40,"line":83},[38,257,52],{"class":51},[38,259,88],{"class":55},[38,261,60],{"class":59},[38,263,264,266,268,270,272],{"class":40,"line":93},[38,265,66],{"class":51},[38,267,98],{"class":59},[38,269,101],{"class":51},[38,271,105],{"class":104},[38,273,108],{"class":59},[38,275,276,278,280],{"class":40,"line":111},[38,277,239],{"class":59},[38,279,242],{"class":55},[38,281,245],{"class":59},[38,283,284,286],{"class":40,"line":119},[38,285,56],{"class":55},[38,287,116],{"class":59},[38,289,290],{"class":40,"line":124},[38,291,75],{"class":59},[38,293,294],{"class":40,"line":129},[38,295,45],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":44},[38,297,298,300,302,304,306],{"class":40,"line":144},[38,299,132],{"class":51},[38,301,98],{"class":59},[38,303,101],{"class":51},[38,305,139],{"class":104},[38,307,108],{"class":59},[38,309,311,314,316],{"class":40,"line":310},13,[38,312,313],{"class":59},"console.",[38,315,242],{"class":55},[38,317,245],{"class":59},[38,319,321,323],{"class":40,"line":320},14,[38,322,147],{"class":55},[38,324,116],{"class":59},[38,326,328,330,332,335,339,342],{"class":40,"line":327},15,[38,329,313],{"class":59},[38,331,242],{"class":55},[38,333,334],{"class":59},"(",[38,336,338],{"class":337},"sTRMh","'what is a now?:'",[38,340,341],{"class":51},"+",[38,343,344],{"class":59}," myVar);\n",[17,346,347],{},"If you've got the idea above down, you can already guess the answer.",[17,349,350],{},[20,351],{"alt":352,"src":353},"The result","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002F4Im2p77.png",[17,355,356,357,360,361,364,365,178],{},"Why doesn't ",[35,358,359],{},"a();"," affect the global scope after it finishes running? Because it got released — it already left the execution stack. So ",[35,362,363],{},"console.log('what is a now?:'+ myVar);"," only ever sees the global variable, which is why the answer is ",[35,366,367],{},"1",[17,369,370,371,374],{},"But what if I actually want to keep the result around? Then I need to write a ",[35,372,373],{},"return"," to hand the result back, like this:",[28,376,378],{"className":30,"code":377,"language":32,"meta":33,"style":33},"function b() {\n var myVar;\n console.log(myVar);\n return myVar\n}\n\nfunction a() {\n var myVar = 2;\n console.log(myVar);\n}\n\nvar myVar = 1;\nconsole.log(myVar);\na();\nvar myVar = b();\nconsole.log('what is a now?:'+ myVar);\n",[35,379,380,388,394,402,410,414,418,426,438,446,450,454,466,474,480,492],{"__ignoreMap":33},[38,381,382,384,386],{"class":40,"line":41},[38,383,52],{"class":51},[38,385,56],{"class":55},[38,387,60],{"class":59},[38,389,390,392],{"class":40,"line":48},[38,391,66],{"class":51},[38,393,69],{"class":59},[38,395,396,398,400],{"class":40,"line":63},[38,397,239],{"class":59},[38,399,242],{"class":55},[38,401,245],{"class":59},[38,403,404,407],{"class":40,"line":72},[38,405,406],{"class":51}," return",[38,408,409],{"class":59}," myVar\n",[38,411,412],{"class":40,"line":78},[38,413,75],{"class":59},[38,415,416],{"class":40,"line":83},[38,417,45],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":44},[38,419,420,422,424],{"class":40,"line":93},[38,421,52],{"class":51},[38,423,88],{"class":55},[38,425,60],{"class":59},[38,427,428,430,432,434,436],{"class":40,"line":111},[38,429,66],{"class":51},[38,431,98],{"class":59},[38,433,101],{"class":51},[38,435,105],{"class":104},[38,437,108],{"class":59},[38,439,440,442,444],{"class":40,"line":119},[38,441,239],{"class":59},[38,443,242],{"class":55},[38,445,245],{"class":59},[38,447,448],{"class":40,"line":124},[38,449,75],{"class":59},[38,451,452],{"class":40,"line":129},[38,453,45],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":44},[38,455,456,458,460,462,464],{"class":40,"line":144},[38,457,132],{"class":51},[38,459,98],{"class":59},[38,461,101],{"class":51},[38,463,139],{"class":104},[38,465,108],{"class":59},[38,467,468,470,472],{"class":40,"line":310},[38,469,313],{"class":59},[38,471,242],{"class":55},[38,473,245],{"class":59},[38,475,476,478],{"class":40,"line":320},[38,477,147],{"class":55},[38,479,116],{"class":59},[38,481,482,484,486,488,490],{"class":40,"line":327},[38,483,132],{"class":51},[38,485,98],{"class":59},[38,487,101],{"class":51},[38,489,56],{"class":55},[38,491,116],{"class":59},[38,493,495,497,499,501,503,505],{"class":40,"line":494},16,[38,496,313],{"class":59},[38,498,242],{"class":55},[38,500,334],{"class":59},[38,502,338],{"class":337},[38,504,341],{"class":51},[38,506,344],{"class":59},[17,508,509],{},[20,510],{"alt":373,"src":511},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FKfO4vQW.png",[17,513,514,515,517,518,520],{},"Pretty neat, right? If you want a function's result to stick around in the global environment after it finishes, you use ",[35,516,373],{}," to send ",[35,519,163],{},"'s execution-context variable back up to the global environment.",[12,522,524],{"id":523},"image-source","Image Source",[17,526,527],{},[147,528,532],{"href":529,"rel":530},"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.udemy.com\u002Fjavascriptjs\u002F",[531],"nofollow","JavaScript Full Guide: Conquering the Weird Parts of JS",[534,535,536],"style",{},"html pre.shiki code .sWyjQ, html code.shiki .sWyjQ{--shiki-default:#FF9492}html pre.shiki code .sj_SG, html code.shiki .sj_SG{--shiki-default:#DBB7FF}html pre.shiki code .sMAXC, html code.shiki .sMAXC{--shiki-default:#F0F3F6}html pre.shiki code .sCcAr, html code.shiki .sCcAr{--shiki-default:#91CBFF}html .default .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}html .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}html pre.shiki code .sTRMh, html code.shiki .sTRMh{--shiki-default:#ADDCFF}",{"title":33,"searchDepth":48,"depth":48,"links":538},[539,540],{"id":14,"depth":48,"text":15},{"id":523,"depth":48,"text":524},"JsWeirdWorld","2019-05-16 13:30:35","The variable environment is really just about where you create your variables. Basically, all you need to care about is \"where\" a variable was created. In this post we walk through a small example that shows how the same variable name can live in three different places without stepping on each other, and how return lets you carry a result back to global scope.","md","en",{},"\u002Fen\u002Fjsweirdworld\u002Fjs-weird-world-09-variable-environments","2",{"title":6,"description":543},false,"en\u002FJsWeirdWorld\u002Fjs-weird-world-09-variable-environments",[553,532],"JavaScript",null,"\u002Fen\u002Fjsweirdworld\u002F2019\u002F05\u002F16\u002Fjs-weird-world-09-variable-environments\u002F","bJzyKCCSOJYjjUALcTLm1Mt0exLal_3LUPnLxPL2lyg",{"newer":558,"older":562},{"url":559,"title":560,"date":561},"\u002Fen\u002Fjsweirdworld\u002F2019\u002F05\u002F16\u002Fjs-weird-world-10-scope-chain\u002F","[JS Weird World] No.10 The Scope Chain","2019-05-16 14:00:35",{"url":563,"title":564,"date":565},"\u002Fen\u002Fhexo\u002F2019\u002F05\u002F16\u002Fnext-hide-disqus-on-tags-categories\u002F","Hide Disqus on NexT Category and Tag Pages","2019-05-16 11:09:29",[567,572,576],{"url":568,"title":569,"date":570,"readingMinutes":571},"\u002Fen\u002Fjsweirdworld\u002F2019\u002F05\u002F27\u002Fjs-weird-world-bonus-closures\u002F","[JS Weird World] Bonus: Closures, One More Time","2019-05-27 13:50:04","5",{"url":573,"title":574,"date":575,"readingMinutes":367},"\u002Fen\u002Fjsweirdworld\u002F2019\u002F05\u002F25\u002Fjs-weird-world-68-the-end-is-a-new-beginning\u002F","[JS Weird World] No.68 Wrapping Up the Weird Parts of JavaScript","2019-05-25 16:36:00",{"url":577,"title":578,"date":579,"readingMinutes":548},"\u002Fen\u002Fjsweirdworld\u002F2019\u002F05\u002F25\u002Fjs-weird-world-67-adding-jquery-support\u002F","[JS Weird World] No.67 Adding jQuery Support to Our Mini Framework","2019-05-25 16:19:00",1784012778039]